{
  "texts": [
    "Cooccurrence analysis was presented in more detail in Sect. 3.1.1 using the VOSviewer software.",
    "In bibliometrics, when we use co-occurrence analysis, we assess academic literature's patterns, progress, and impact quantitatively, providing a comprehensive picture of a field of research.",
    "However, for an in-depth semantic analysis, it is necessary to combine bibliomet-Fig. 6 Co-occurrence network map of terms 1 3 ric analysis studies with other text-data mining analysis (Hu et al. 2014).",
    "Therefore, topic modelling studies extend the scope of bibliometric analysis studies and enable more detailed analyses.",
    "Topic modelling is a method that uses probability to uncover hidden semantic patterns on texts (Blei et al. 2003)."
  ]
}